Yosano Says Japan Economy Improving, Sees China, Oil as Risks

-- B y   M a y u m i   O t s u m a
-- 
2011-03-07T23:58:03Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-07/yosano-says-japan-economy-improving-sees-china-oil-as-risks.html
Japan’s Economic and Fiscal Policy
Minister  Kaoru Yosano  said the nation’s economy is improving,
while higher commodity prices and Chinese inflation pose
downside risks.  Yosano, speaking to reporters in Tokyo today, also said
that the climb in oil costs may gradually hurt the global
economy.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mayumi Otsuma in Tokyo at 
